scene.message:
Nanjo: "...cure what ails you,{nl}
reach for Disick~"{waitkey}What is this jingle?!{nl}
It'll brainwash you!{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: The only thing you can{nl}
trust is your own strength...{nl}
A sound way of thinking.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: So this is Tadashi's{nl}
uncle's shop, huh.{waitkey}{clearbox}He said his family runs a{nl}
shop in Mikage Sun Mall,{nl}
right?{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: It's a wonder{nl}
Sonomura's mom even made it{nl}
to the shrine.{waitkey}If she'd collapsed on the{nl}
way, she might've ended up{nl}
demon prey...{wait_fr:32} I suppose.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: I, too, wish to unravel{nl}
this mystery with my own{nl}
hands.{waitkey}It's a chance to put all I've{nl}
learned to good use, after{nl}
all.{waitkey}{ret}

Shopkeeper: Are you all{nl}
friends of my nephew Tadashi?{nl}
If so, I'll give you a deal!{waitkey}{ret}

Shopkeeper: I'm not the least{nl}
bit scared of demons, no~{waitkey}{clearbox}Those things are bound to be{nl}
a trick of the eye or some{nl}
kind of hoax!{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: When I went to the{nl}
park, there was a tree I'd{nl}
never seen before. It's neat,{nl}
why not go have a look?{waitkey}{ret}

Shopkeeper: That's my private{nl}
room over there~ So you're{nl}
not allowed in, okay~{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: The TV and radio{nl}
are both dead, and my parents{nl}
are cowering under the{nl}
covers...{waitkey}In the end, you've just got{nl}
to sort things out yourself.{waitkey}{ret}
